Vice President Mike Pence visited Performance Advantage Company in Lancaster, New York to discuss tax cuts. Pence outlined the key elements of the proposed tax cut plan, including lowering tax rates for working families, simplifying the tax code, and lowering taxes on American businesses. He listened to the concerns and thoughts of business owners and emphasized the importance of tax relief for American families and creating jobs. The Vice President also highlighted the need to lower taxes on small businesses and discussed the potential benefits of immediate expensing of capital investments. Pence assured the business owners that their input would be taken into account as the tax cut plan is debated in Congress.